  "_models_comment": "Per-model combat ratings from the Tank & Gun Characteristics Charts (4.47/4.48/4.49), extracted this session. A unit may name a 'model' to override its role's combat ratings (only the fields present are overridden; steps/cpa/mobility stay from the role). Tank models set oca/dca/anti_armor/armor_protection/is_tank; gun models set anti_armor/vulnerability; artillery set barrage/vulnerability (25pdr also anti_armor).",
  "_bar_comment": "'bar' = Breakdown Adjustment Rating (rule 21.3), the per-model column shift applied on the [21.38] Breakdown Table BEFORE rolling. Signed integer convention: +N = N columns to the RIGHT (more breakdown, less reliable), -N = N LEFT, 0 = none. Sources: German [4.49], Italian [4.48], and Commonwealth [4.47] Tank & Gun Characteristics Charts (see data/breakdown_rates.json 'bar_by_model' for the full recovered chart, incl. the CW column that had to be read off the PDF scan and the trucks' 54.2 -2). German tanks: all 0 (chart note *: temporarily +1 / 1R until Game-Turn 1/31 -- a turn-gate to honor in the reader, not a flat value). Gun/AT/artillery models carry NO 'bar': towed guns with inherent transport never break down (21.11), a '-' on the chart. DATA ONLY -- no engine code reads 'bar' yet.",
